- CF Release version: 239
- Diego version: 0.1481.0
- Garden version: 0.339
- CF MySQL version: 26.2
- etcd version: 60
- Apps Manager release version: 642
- UAA version: 3.4.2
- Consul version: 97
- CF Routing release: 0.135
- PCF Service Backup release: 14
- PCF MySQL Backup release: 1.25
- Pivotal Account app: 1
- PCF Autoscale: 34
- PCF Notifications: 24
- cflinuxfs2-rootfs: 1.20 (the rootfs is updated frequently, so please refer to the the patch release notes below to see what version was used in each)
- Python Buildpack now includes Conda package manager



### Routing

- TCP Routing enables developers to run applications on PCF that support non-HTTP TCP protocols. Please see [this topic](need link here) for more information.
- - In support of this, Routing components fetch tokens from UAA by calling that component directly over TLS. The cert hosted by UAA is generated by Operations Manager.
- Some processes on the Gorouter job no longer run as root.
- Route services whose domain names are resolved using EDNS0 are now supported.


### Authenitcation and Authorization

- Apps Manager now supports inviting external users from LDAP & SAML user stores. Please refer to the [Link Topic] for more details. 

- PCF Admin role can now be derived from SAML group memberships. Please refer to the [Link Topic] for more details.

- Basic User Attributes including First Name, Last Name and Email can now be derived from the the SAML or LDAP enabled external user store. Please refer to [Link Topic] for more details.

- The Login prompts displayed on the Login Page and in the CF CLI can now be configured. Please refer to [Link Topic] for more details.

- New API Docs for UAA are now available at http://docs.cloudfoundry.org/api/uaa/

### Docker Proxy server

This feature allows you to put a proxy server between your PCF deployment and Docker Hub, for access to image files.

Please see [this topic](need link here) for more information.

### Unpriviledged App Containers

You can now switch off priviledged containers for your applications.

Please see [this topic - needs link updated when 1.8 docs published](http://docs-pcf-staging.cfapps.io/pivotalcf/1-8/concepts/container-security.html) for more information.

### AWS SSE-S3

Blobstores for Cloud Controller can now be encrypted at rest using SSE-S3. Existing blobs will not be encrypted.

Please see [this topic - needs link updated when 1.8 docs published](http://docs-pcf-staging.cfapps.io/pivotalcf/1-8/customizing/pcf-aws-manual-er-config.html#file-store-config) for more information.

### API Environment Variable Visibility

Similar to `space_developer_env_var_visibility`, there is a new feature flag, `env_var_visibility` that can be disabled to disallow all users, including administrators, access to `/v2/apps/:guid/env`. 
